<p>
This grading form expands the <a href="grading-form.pdf">Program
    Style Summary and Checklist</a> that applies to all program development
    in CSC 161.
</p>

<p>
This project will be worth 25 points, based on the following rubric:

</p>

<ul>
<li>
control of robot activities (5 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<li>
program can perform at least 10 separate commands (10 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<li>
description and steps for testing (5 points
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<li>
creativity in making an interesting robot application (5 points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<li>
Neatness and conciseness of code <br>
(no points earned, but difficulties could deduct points)
<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>

</ul>


<p>
Form updated:  2 April 2013
</p>

